---
import { cloudinaryUrl } from '../utils/cloudinary';

// Swap this public_id when you upload your portrait to Cloudinary
const portraitUrl = cloudinaryUrl('portfolio/about/portrait', 'f_auto,q_auto,w_600,h_750,c_fill,g_face');
---

<section id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row g-5 align-items-start">

      <div class="col-lg-4 reveal">
        <div class="about-portrait">
          <img
            src={portraitUrl}
            alt="Paul Rojas"
            width="600"
            height="750"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-lg-8 reveal">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">About</p>
        <h2 class="section-title mb-4" style="font-size:clamp(1.6rem,3vw,2.2rem);">
          The photographer behind the camera.
        </h2>

        <div class="about-body">
          <p>
            My name is <strong>Paul Rojas</strong>. I shoot film — mostly street, mostly in places
            where nobody's watching. The name of this site isn't a mystery: most of my best rolls
            happen on completely unremarkable days that I only remember because I had a camera.
          </p>
          <p>
            I started shooting in the analogue dark — expired rolls, broken light seals, cameras
            that required a certain relationship before they'd work right. The Nikkormat and I have
            come to an understanding.
          </p>
          <p>
            I also shoot with a Fujifilm X-T20 body. Not as a concession to convenience — the
            simulations matter. Classic Chrome reads like a faded print. Acros renders shadows the
            way HC-110 used to. The intent is the same; the chemistry is just different.
          </p>
          <p>
            I don't bracket. I don't shoot in burst. Every frame has a cost, and that cost makes
            you pay attention.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="camera-note">
          <strong>Currently shooting:</strong>&nbsp; Nikkormat FT2 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
          Nikon 50mm f/1.4 AI &nbsp;·&nbsp; Konica 100 VX / Kodak Color 200&nbsp;<br />
          <strong>Developing:</strong>&nbsp; HC-110 (Dilution B) &nbsp;·&nbsp; D-76 1:1<br />
          <strong>Also shooting:</strong>&nbsp; Fujifilm X-T20 &nbsp;·&nbsp;
          Classic Chrome &nbsp;·&nbsp; Acros &nbsp;·&nbsp; Eterna Cinema
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
